832
00:39:01,090 --> 00:39:02,110
I DO look

833
00:39:02,110 --> 00:39:05,310
I do look at the price but since I want cabbages I buy it

834
00:39:05,310 --> 00:39:07,780
It wouldn't be 1000 yen for one cabbage would it?

835
00:39:07,780 --> 00:39:10,400
She's really staring me down

836
00:39:10,400 --> 00:39:13,170
You were smiling when talking to Matsumoto-san

837
00:39:13,170 --> 00:39:15,670
She got excited and really stared me down

838
00:39:15,670 --> 00:39:19,100
This time I have brought a theory about those point cards

839
00:39:19,100 --> 00:39:21,410
Here it is:

840
00:39:21,410 --> 00:39:26,100
Theory: There are plenty of point cards that set goals that are impossible to reach

841
00:39:28,220 --> 00:39:30,300
Ones that make you think "Can you really save up from that?"

842
00:39:30,300 --> 00:39:32,930
"How many times will I have to go there?"

843
00:39:32,930 --> 00:39:35,680
There are plenty like that...

844
00:39:33,700 --> 00:39:35,680
Oh really...

845
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:41,000
We will investigate some point cards that are hard to accomplish or are plain weird after this

846
00:39:42,320 --> 00:39:48,990
We will investigate the theory that there are plenty of point cards that set goals that are impossible to reach

847
00:39:49,410 --> 00:39:53,050
Now, when we search for them...

848
00:39:53,050 --> 00:39:57,920
